'''Nadine Pidjot''' (born 1967) is a lawyer from New Caledonia. She was the first [[Kanak people|Kanak]] woman to become a lawyer.<ref name=":0">{{Cite news|url=http://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/nouvellecaledonie/nadine-pidjot-premiere-femme-kanak-avocate-470251.html|title=Nadine Pidjot, première femme kanak avocate - nouvelle calédonie 1ère|work=nouvelle calédonie 1ère|access-date=2017-11-19}}</ref>

Pidjot was born in Conception, New Caledonia, in 1967.<ref name=":1">{{Cite news|url=http://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/nouvellecaledonie/nadine-pidjot-prete-serment-474787.html|title=Nadine Pidjot a prêté serment - nouvelle calédonie 1ère|work=nouvelle calédonie 1ère|access-date=2017-11-19}}</ref> She studied general law, completing a master's degree. She worked at the High Commission of the Republic of New Caledonia and the French Embassy in Australia.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.spc.int/70-oceaniennes-dexception/nadine-pidjot/?lang=fr|title=Nadine Pidjot|date=2017-09-08|work=SPC Corporate Site|access-date=2017-11-19|language=fr-FR}}</ref> In 2006, Pidjot joined the administration of the Government of New Caledonia. In 2013 she left, and founded her own consulting firm.<ref name=":0" />

In May 2017, Pidjot was admitted to the bar, becoming the first Kanak woman lawyer.<ref name=":1" />

